Wash and dry all produce. Trim and thinly slice @Persian cucumber{1%unit} crosswise into
rounds. Halve @lime{1%unit}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine cucumber, juice from lime halves, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}.
Set aside to pickle.

Roughly chop @peanuts{½%ounce}.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon} and @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce}.

Add @shredded red cabbage{4%ounce} and toss to coat. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Pat @diced steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}.

> Use a meat pat to press the steak dry - this helps achieve a good sear.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over high heat. Add
steak and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Reduce heat to medium, then pour in @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon}. Cook until glaze
has thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Turn off
heat.

While steak cooks, wrap @flour tortillas{6%unit} in damp #paper towels{}. Microwave
until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates and fill with steak, slaw, pickled cucumber
(draining first), and peanuts. Serve.